claim.claim-text:
1. A system for modeling a communications network, comprising:
a three dimensional environmental computer database model of a site where a communications network may be deployed;
a display for displaying a three-dimensional site map of said site, the three-dimensional site map including non-network elements;
means for selecting computer representations of one or more components which may be used in said communications network from amongst a database of computer representations of components, said computer representations of each of said one or more components comprising performance data;
means for positioning said one or more components on said three-dimensional site map of said site;
means for calculating one or more performance characteristics of said communications network modeled by said three dimensional environmental computer database model; and
means for displaying, on said three-dimensional site map of said site displayed on said display, a graphical rendering of said one or more performance characteristics.

29. A method for modeling a communications network, comprising:
providing a three dimensional environmental computer database model of a site where a communications network may be deployed;
displaying a three-dimensional site map of said site, the three-dimensional site map including non-network elements;
selecting computer representations of one or more components which may be used in said communications network from amongst a database of computer representations of components, said computer representations of each of said one or more components comprising performance data;
positioning said one or more components on said three-dimensional site map of said site;
calculating one or more performance characteristics of said communications network modeled by said three dimensional environmental computer database model; and
displaying, on said three-dimensional site map, a graphical rendering of said one or more performance characteristics.

55. A system for modeling a communications network, comprising:
a three dimensional environmental computer database model of a site including non-network elements where a communications network may be deployed with computer representations of one or more components which may be used in the communications network positioned within a site map of said site, said computer representations of said one or more components being selectable from a database which comprises a plurality of computer representations wherein each of said computer representations comprises performance characteristics;
a display for displaying a three-dimensional site map of said site;
means for calculating performance characteristics of said communications network modeled by said three dimensional environmental computer database model;
means for displaying, on said three-dimensional site map of said site displayed on said display, a graphical rendering of said one or more performance characteristics; and
means for changing
a) a computer representation of at least one component at one or more positions within said site map of said site, or
b) a position of a computer representation of at least one component within said site map of said site, or
c) an orientation of a component modeled by said computer representation of at least one component within said site map of said site, or
d) an interconnection between computer representations of at least two components.

72. A method for modeling a communications network, comprising:
providing a three dimensional environmental computer database model of a site where a communication s network may be deployed with computer representations of one or more components which may be used in the communications network positioned within a site map of said site, said computer representations of said one or more components being selectable from a database which comprises a plurality of computer representation s wherein each of said computer representations comprises performance characteristics;
displaying a three-dimensional site map of said site, the three-dimensional site map including non-network elements;
calculating performance characteristics of said communications network modeled by said three dimensional environmental computer database model;
displaying on said three-dimensional site map a graphical rendering of said one or more performance characteristics; and
changing at least one of
a) a computer representation of at least one component at one or more positions within said site map of said site, or
b) a position of a computer representation of at least one component within said site map of said site, or
c) an orientation of a component modeled by said computer representation of at least one component within said site map of said site; or
d) an interconnection between computer representations of at least two components.
